## Follow-up (outside this PR)

The real prevention for token expiration requires changes in the **`getsentry/publish`** workflow — either:

- Create a fresh token after the Docker container exits and run the merge as a separate step
- Or: switch Craft's merge to use the GitHub merge API (`POST /repos/{owner}/{repo}/merges`), then update the workflow to provide a fresh token for that API call

This is tracked separately since it involves cross-repo coordination.
